cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.HC 

The paper discusses security and trust-related challenges in the global IC manufacturing supply chain, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of hardware obfuscation mechanisms, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) and embedded systems (cs.ET). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) due to the vulnerabilities in hardware obfuscation mechanisms.
